
18-Sep-97 rr@sco.com

Install povray-3.02-dist.tar.gz as follows :

    # su
    # cd /
    # gzcat <path-to-archive>/povray-3.02-dist.tar.gz | tar xf -

In order to customize the behaviour of povray,
copy the file /usr/local/lib/povray3/povray.ini
into $HOME/.povrayrc and tailor it to your taste.

To test the installation, after performing the above steps,
run the command :

    $ povray +i witch.pov

This should produce the file witch.tga in the current directory.
To view this, use any Targa file format viewer. For instance,
install ImageMagick and run the command :

    $ display witch.tga
